			<h2>Veterinary and Other Care</h2>

			<p>AHAS Home Veterinary Services provides no-cost veterinary services in Edmonton to qualified clients who are not able to access regular veterinary care, including:</p>

			<ul>
				<li>Wellness Exams</li>
				<li>Vaccinations</li>
				<li>Internal and External Parasite Treatment</li>
				<li>Radiography</li>
				<li>Laboratory Analysis</li>
				<li>Emergency grooming with sedation (we are NOT a grooming service)</li>
				<li>Spay/neuter surgery (please apply to the PALS program at the Edmonton Humane Society for spay/neuter for dogs under seven years of age)</li>
				<li>Dental Care (please note we have a very long wait for dental surgery)</li>
				<li>Chronic illness support</li>
				<li>Behaviour and Nutrition Counseling</li>
				<li>Discussion and Support for Housing Concerns</li>
				<li>Euthanasia</li>
			</ul>

		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Requirements for Eligibility</h2>

			<p>AHAS Home Veterinary Services provides basic veterinary care to people living with a very low income in Edmonton.  Our policy is to ensure all patients are spayed/neutered as long as they are healthy; we will not see your pets if you will not spay/neuter them.</p>

