		<h2>Apply for Services here: Request our services</h2>

		<p>PLEASE NOTE:  It may take a few days to get back to you but you will receive an email asking to send in qualifying information.  Please do not call or email us to see if we have received your application as it slows down our volunteers.</p>

		<p>PLEASE NOTE:  We are not able to offer urgent services to new clients except under extraordinary circumstances.  If you have an urgent need, please contact an emergency clinic near you.</p>

		<p>If you need spay/neuter services for a young, healthy dog, please apply to the PALS program at the Edmonton Humane Society:  https://www.edmontonhumanesociety.com/services/pals-spay-and-neuter-program/</p>

		[[ Food Bank ]]

		<h2>Nearby Pet Food Banks</h2>

		<p>Veterinary costs aside, pet owners face the additional costs of keeping their furry friends well-fed, healthy and happy.</p>

		If you are short of food and/or supplies, check out the following:
		<ul>
			<li>Inner City Pet Food Bank, Bissell Centre, 10527 – 96 Street, Wednesdays 10 – 12.</li>

			<li>Bethel Gospel Chapel, 11461 – 95 Street, Mondays 3 – 5.</li>

			<li>Parachutes for Pets Edmonton, 8108 Coronet Road.  Call 587-598-7723 or email edmonton@parachutesforpets.com to book a time to pick up food.</li>

			<li>Many groups on Facebook can help with food.  Search for “pet food bank” for help.</li>

			<li>Edmonton Food Bank may have some food and supplies as well</li>
		</ul>
		<p>We have some food as well.  You can also check out our “After Hours Pet Food Bank” box in our parking lot behind the clinic</p>


		<h2>How Can You Help?</h2>

		<p>Take your food donation to Bissell Centre, 10527 – 96 Street NW, Monday – Friday 9 – 12 or 1 – 4</p>

		<p>We can also accept small amounts of food and supplies.  Drop off at the clinic, 12701 – 119 Street NW, Monday- Friday 10- 4</p>

